OpenHarmony QEMU ARM Linux-6.6 MD Stop Writes Fix Patch

This patch fixes the __md_stop_writes() function in drivers/md/md.c to
match the upstream linux-6.6 kernel API.

Root cause: The OpenHarmony kernel source contains a broken version of
__md_stop_writes() that:
1. References sync_work instead of del_work (upstream changed the field name)
2. Wraps quiesce and bitmap flush in a broken conditional using mddev_is_dm()
   and md_bitmap_enabled() / bitmap_ops->flush() which are not present in 6.6
3. Has a malformed if statement missing the "if" keyword and md_is_rdwr()

The fix aligns the function with the actual upstream linux-6.6 implementation:
- Use del_work instead of sync_work
- Make quiesce unconditional (no mddev_is_dm wrapper)
- Use md_bitmap_flush() instead of md_bitmap_enabled/bitmap_ops->flush
- Properly form the if condition with md_is_rdwr(mddev) &&

diff -Naur a/drivers/md/md.c b/drivers/md/md.c
--- a/drivers/md/md.c	2026-05-19 14:27:18.892122654 +0800
+++ b/drivers/md/md.c	2026-05-30 16:50:02.797210990 +0800
@@ -6299,7 +6299,7 @@
 static void __md_stop_writes(struct mddev *mddev)
 {
 	set_bit(MD_RECOVERY_FROZEN, &mddev->recovery);
-	if (work_pending(&mddev->sync_work))
+	if (work_pending(&mddev->del_work))
 		flush_workqueue(md_misc_wq);
 	if (mddev->sync_thread) {
 		set_bit(MD_RECOVERY_INTR, &mddev->recovery);
@@ -6308,15 +6308,13 @@
 
 	del_timer_sync(&mddev->safemode_timer);
 
-	if (md_is_rdwr(mddev) || !mddev_is_dm(mddev)) {
-		if (mddev->pers && mddev->pers->quiesce) {
-			mddev->pers->quiesce(mddev, 1);
-			mddev->pers->quiesce(mddev, 0);
-		}
-
-		if (md_bitmap_enabled(mddev, true))
-			mddev->bitmap_ops->flush(mddev);
+	if (mddev->pers && mddev->pers->quiesce) {
+		mddev->pers->quiesce(mddev, 1);
+		mddev->pers->quiesce(mddev, 0);
 	}
+	md_bitmap_flush(mddev);
+
+	if (md_is_rdwr(mddev) &&
 	    ((!mddev->in_sync && !mddev_is_clustered(mddev)) ||
 	     mddev->sb_flags)) {
 		/* mark array as shutdown cleanly */
